==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Felt
<hw>Felt</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <def><pos>imp. & p. p. ⟦or⟧ a.</pos> from
<er>Feel</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Felt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Felt
<hw>Felt</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>felt</ets>;
akin to D. <ets>vilt</ets>, G. <ets>filz</ets>, and possibly to Gr. <?/
hair or wool wrought into felt, L. <ets>pilus</ets> hair,
<ets>pileus</ets> a felt cap or hat.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A cloth or
stuff made of matted fibers of wool, or wool and fur, fulled or wrought
into a compact substance by rolling and pressure, with lees or size,
without spinning or weaving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It were a delicate stratagem to shoe⟦br⟧
A troop of horse with felt.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A hat made of felt.</def>
<rj><au>Thynne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A skin or hide; a fell; a pelt.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To know whether sheep are sound or not, see that the
<qex>felt</qex> be loose.</q> <rj><qau>Mortimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col>Felt grain</col>, <cd>the grain of timber which is
transverse to the annular rings or plates; the direction of the
medullary rays in oak and some other timber.</cd>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Felt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Felt
<hw>Felt</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Felted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Felting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make into felt, or
a feltike substance; to cause to adhere and mat together.</def>
<rj><au>Sir M. Hale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cover with, or as with, felt; <as>as, to
<ex>felt</ex> the cylinder of a steam engine</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Felter</ent>⟦br⟧
